name: Torpid Slivers 34: Velchzinger's Hand
description: Fig.17(c): The mating columnhoppers (Stictocephala capitellum) will not be happy until they can replicate in silhouette the hand of the entomologist T. Velchzinger, their dear departed keeper. Only then will the wallpaper pattern rotate 45 degrees to the east (for unknown reasons).
